phrases: TL note: Shiritori is a Japanese word game in which the players are required to say a word which begins with the final kana of the previous word.
I just realised it for the first time
That I had fallen in love
Twenty-four hours a day thinking of you, you and nothing more than you!
It is something I was not consciously aware of
Somehow ( somehow) I am feeling different from the usual
With you ( the two of us) and our dull chatter
Do not tell me ( mutual love?)
Nope, it is a one-sided crush
Why is my heart pounding like this?
Did a short circuit just make a mess out of my mind?
This is my first time... feeling like this...
I wonder if I have a fever
Suddenly and precipitately, love has arrived.
Instantly igniting my face into a bright red
Is this really what they call love?
I want to know your feelings.
I feel I could fly towards the sky
Woke up in the morning, brushed my teeth
In the blink of an eye, it is 10pm
Today, we laughed a whole lot
At times, with my friends, acting like fools, being noisy
I would not call this my first love
Say, will we be able to meet again tomorrow?
I see you sparkling all over the place
Today was fun, too, was not it?
It is my pleasure to meet you, my new-found love.
Surely, we will meet again tomorrow
We will meet immediately in our dreams
I am really hungry, so this is perfect.
I put something in for a hidden taste.
I wonder if you can tell.
Having a hidden taste makes it sound like the real thing.
It only has the miso flavour, or rather,
the hidden taste is not so hidden, or rather...
No, instead, the more you chew it,
the hidden taste gets worse, or rather...
I am really against this hidden taste!
TL note: Kappa, literally meaning river-child, is a water sprite found in Japanese folklore.
Why a kappa all of the sudden?
Moreover, what does she mean by is cool, is not it?...
Next time, I might want to draw something in fantasy that is interesting and strong.
Something like a Daidarabotchi and a kappa.
TL note: Daidarabotchi is a gigantic demon in Japanese mythology.
Heh, I guess he will be the uke.
TL note: In yaoi, uke refers to the more feminine partner.
With this, maybe we can just play picture shiritori.
TL note: In Japanese, parasite is read as parasaito, but Yukko read it as parashite.
This is what a parashite's meant to be like?
She is inviting me to a game of picture shiritori.
She read parasite's to as te.
What the hell is a tengo?!
There is no way a high school student would make such a childish mistake.
I mean, she already drew a picture of a tengu and still wrote down what it was.
I do not really understand, but...
I guess I will go with go here.
What is with this Goku drawn out of boredom?
TL note: Goku is a character from a classical Chinese novel Journey To The West.
I am pretty sure I drew a tengu just now...
Well, I can understand how she could mistake gu for go.
I will get juice from her later for this.
Now, it is you... you... you...
TL note: Sea urchin is uni, and rabbit is usagi, or usa for short, in Japanese.
TL note: Cow is ushi in Japanese.
She came at me with the tongue!
TL note: In Japanese, tongue is shita.
If you write it like this, it is not a taxi.
I am just going to write down whatever works.
Oh, seafood has started to come up!
She is really up for it.
TL note: There is no word in Japanese beginning with the sound n, so you lose if you use a word ending with the kana n in a game of shiritori.
I just have to do this...
Ah, there is nothing to do.
There is nothing to do, Sekiguchi.
Okay, Sekiguchi, let us have an Isse no se match!
TL note: Isse no se is a Japanese numbers game played using both hands.
There is nothing to do, anyway.
Cannot you play with me sometimes?
I forgot my homework and was made to stand in the hallway, Mogami river.
I cannot believe I have to stand in the hallway just because I forgot my homework today...
How should I spend this time, Mogami river.
W-Why is the principal is trying to catch the deer...?
TL note: Shika senbei are rice crackers specially made to feed deer.
W-Wai - Everyone, the principal is d-dyin -
And falls down just like that!
Nothing new to report from the hallway!
Those were the true words that came from the bottom of her heart.
They were by no means to cover up for the principal,
nor because explaining it would be too troublesome.
Maybe she just wanted to show respect to the heroes who had just performed a fight to the death.
It is too early to gather the early-summer rain, Mogami river.
You do not need a referee for ten yen soccer.
You do not understand, do you?
It is all about the feeling, the feeling.
I guess it cannot be helped.
Come at me from any angle!
First comes rock, next comes paper.
Anyway, I will have to do it carefully...
I have to make sure this disgusting root of evil does not spread in the house again.
A plan... I have to go with the most perfect plan...
It is not a one-hit-kill, so there is a chance that it will just run away.
I do not want to see it squirm!
I will cover the tea table with detergent to seal its movement, and then pinpoint it directly!
With nowhere to run, it will definitely fly!
When it flies, it is over.
It will blindly aim somewhere and hit people!
If it were to hit my body... or hit my face...!
I-If this was to get inside... get inside my mouth...
It is a one-shot rock and roll!
This is the worst kind of uneasiness.
I do not have any other choice.
The choice of lifting this bowl up might kill me!
There is no choice but to do that...
I-Inside this, there is a r-roach... a roach.
I guess it cannot be helped.
I will get it, so lift the bowl.
No, I am saying lift the bowl.
How could I lift the seal on the root of evil?!
The moment I lift it up, it is death or die!
How am I supposed to get it without lifting up the bowl?!
The professor is not bothered by bugs either, so surely she can...
Professor, i-it would be nice if you could get rid of t-this cockroach inside this bowl!
Sorry, then I shall leave it to you.
I will do it in one shot!
TL note: Men is what you say after successfully hitting your opponent's head in kendo.
Oh, I hit the wrong one.
I am seriously worried here, but this person is... this person is...
Geez, there is no way I would hate you.
Now, it is time to rock and roll!
Hey, it is hot, so can I get out?
Then let us get out after a count to ten.
You said we can get out once we count to ten.
You have to say One, two...
Just because they have cram school, they all leave.
Sekiguchi, you are bored as well, right?
Come to think of it, did not you go to cram school, too?
You have got to be kidding!
Mai-chan, how are things over there?
It seems like it is ready.
The extremely delicious super-curry is complete.
I think it will take a little longer over here.
We should have started these before the curry.
Even if a baby is crying from hunger, do not remove the lid.
Ah, we should have brought mayonnaise.
You really need mayonnaise for curry.
Yukko, what do you like with curry?
T-This is... not what you think...
I still have - Look, I still have tokoroten!
TL note: Tokoroten are strips of gelidium jelly (agar).
What is the colour of your blood?!
We have lost the curry and rice we were having for lunch.
There is still tokoroten, if you want...
I think we should take turns eating it.
However, as we are to blame, Mai-chan, you should start.
Just make sure you do not eat all of it in one bite!
I am not a demon, you know.
this will end as a disappointing camping trip!
Let us play cards at the very last moment and give it a happy ending!
Adults drink alcohol at times like these, right?
Hey, Mai-chan, do not you agree?
Exit the bath, drink milk, act drunk.
TL note: Wadoukaichin is Japan's first circulated coinage, minted in 708 CE.
A person's value is not measured by money!
The next Nichijou is the seventh!
